698a6eb9-82ea-4eb1-8915-f61a7feae57c	Project Requirements & Use Cases	Understand the project requirements and use cases. Study similar existing protocols (NFT marketplaces, staking platforms, etc.)	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	2026-05-04 18:49:36.888	2026-05-04 18:49:36.888	2026-05-04 17:45:35.504	2026-05-04 18:49:36.888	7c1ce787-d304-4d76-bbf2-279ea0a2508c	The DAO Governance Platform enables decentralized decision-making where no single authority controls the system. Instead, governance is handled collectively by token holders through proposals and voting.\nProblem Statement:\nTraditional decision-making systems are centralized, leading to limited transparency and control. This project solves that by allowing all stakeholders to participate in governance in a transparent and trustless manner using blockchain technology.\nTarget Users:\n- Token holders who want to participate in governance\n- DAO members responsible for decision-making\n- Organizations aiming for decentralized control\nKey Use Cases:\n1. Proposal Creation:\n   Any authorized user can create a proposal with a title and description to suggest changes or actions within the DAO.\n2. Voting Mechanism:\n   Token holders can vote "Yes" or "No" on proposals. Voting power can be proportional to token ownership.\n3. Vote Tracking & Transparency:\n   All votes are recorded on the blockchain, ensuring immutability and transparency.\n4. Proposal Status & Deadline:\n   Each proposal has a voting deadline. Users can view active, completed, and executed proposals.\n5. Proposal Execution:\n   If a proposal passes the required criteria (e.g., majority votes), it is marked as approved and can be executed.\n6. Wallet Integration:\n   Users connect via wallets like MetaMask to securely interact with the platform.\nReference Systems:\nThis project is inspired by real-world DAO platforms such as Snapshot (off-chain voting) and Compound Governance (on-chain voting).\nExpected Outcome:\nA functional decentralized governance system where users can create proposals, vote securely, and view transparent results on-chain.	https://github.com/jahnaviyakkala/dao-governance	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
23ee9a77-7c4a-4b49-b0ee-2fb90d5d21d7	Final Project Selection	Choose one final project:\n\n NFT Marketplace, \nDeFi Staking Platform, \nToken Vesting System, \nMini DEX, \nDAO Governance Platform	1e9350df-d635-4e50-862a-e7f5f5b9f5d6	\N	running	medium	\N	\N	intern	1e9350df-d635-4e50-862a-e7f5f5b9f5d6	\N	\N	2026-05-05 09:53:54.47	2026-05-05 09:53:59.25	82efb126-12c4-4cd2-a316-1b19ed8a987c	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
f2b2dec6-2cbd-4167-b49a-a14b4b3d6ce6	System Architecture Design	Design system architecture and smart contract logic. Prepare technical documentation and workflow diagrams	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	2026-05-04 19:21:38.207	2026-05-04 19:21:38.207	2026-05-04 17:45:48.486	2026-05-04 19:21:38.208	f24f6c81-2a83-490f-bfa5-a17f30a959f8	The DAO Governance Platform follows a modular architecture consisting of smart contracts (backend), a React-based frontend, wallet integration, and blockchain interaction.\nSystem Components:\n1. Smart Contracts (Solidity):\nThe core logic is implemented using multiple smart contracts:\n- GovernanceToken: ERC20Votes token used for voting power with snapshot functionality.\n- GovernorContract: Manages proposal creation, voting, quorum validation, and execution flow.\n- Timelock: Adds a delay before executing approved proposals for security.\n- Box: A sample governed contract used to demonstrate execution of proposals.\n2. Frontend (React + Ethers.js):\nThe frontend provides a user interface for interacting with the DAO. Users can:\n- Connect their wallet (MetaMask)\n- Create proposals\n- View proposals\n- Vote on proposals\n3. Wallet Integration:\nMetaMask is used for authentication and transaction signing. All actions such as proposal creation and voting require user approval via wallet.\n4. Blockchain Network:\nThe system runs on a local Hardhat network, where all smart contracts are deployed and executed.\nWorkflow:\n1. User connects wallet via frontend  \n2. User creates a proposal → transaction sent to GovernorContract  \n3. Proposal is stored on-chain  \n4. Token holders vote (Yes/No) → voting power determined by GovernanceToken snapshot  \n5. Votes are recorded and validated by GovernorContract  \n6. If proposal meets quorum → queued in Timelock  \n7. After delay → proposal executed on target contract (Box)  \nDesign Considerations:\n- Security: Timelock prevents immediate execution of proposals  \n- Fair Voting: Snapshot mechanism avoids vote manipulation  \n- Transparency: All actions are recorded on-chain  \n- Modularity: Separate contracts improve scalability and maintainability  \nThis architecture ensures a secure, transparent, and decentralized governance system aligned with industry standards.	https://github.com/jahnaviyakkala/dao-governance	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
614b7e77-5435-4446-bf1a-03b840ef3dfb	Wallet Connection Integration	Connect wallet functionality (MetaMask, WalletConnect, Coinbase Wallet) to the DApp	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	2026-05-05 06:40:27.945	2026-05-05 06:40:27.945	2026-05-04 17:47:22.38	2026-05-05 06:40:27.945	2a73a7a6-b539-4690-b3f4-814f234dc01e	In this phase, I implemented wallet connection functionality to enable users to securely interact with the DAO Governance Platform using MetaMask.\n\nWallet Integration:\n\nMetaMask was integrated using Ethers.js to allow users to connect their accounts directly from the browser. Upon connection, the application retrieves the user’s wallet address and uses it to initialize a signer for executing transactions.\n\nKey Functionalities:\n\n1. Wallet Connection:\n- Users can connect their MetaMask wallet through a connect button\n- The application requests account access using the Ethereum provider\n\n2. Signer & Provider Setup:\n- A Web3 provider is created using Ethers.js\n- A signer is derived from the connected wallet to authorize transactions\n\n3. Transaction Signing:\n- All blockchain interactions such as proposal creation, voting, and execution are signed using the user’s wallet\n- No private keys are stored in the application, ensuring security\n\n4. Account Handling:\n- The application detects and updates when the user switches accounts\n- Displays the connected wallet address in the UI\n\n5. Network Handling:\n- Basic checks are implemented to ensure the user is connected to the correct network (Hardhat local network)\n\nSecurity Considerations:\n\n- All transactions require explicit user approval via MetaMask\n- Sensitive operations are handled entirely through the wallet\n- No centralized storage of user credentials\n\nNote:\nThe current implementation uses MetaMask as the primary wallet. The architecture can be extended to support WalletConnect and Coinbase Wallet for broader compatibility.	https://github.com/jahnaviyakkala/dao-governance	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
