cd621568-597c-4e9e-a3ac-972d54ce4fd6	HelloWorld Smart Contract	Deploy smart contract on SCAI mainnet network and remix IDE \nYou can get SCAI Mainnet coins using faucet: https://faucet.securechain.ai \nAnd you can add SCAI Mainnet in your metamask from the faucet website itself.\nMore details about SCAI mainnet: https://chainlist.org/chain/34 	c3a9c478-15f3-418f-99b6-fbd068756dc8	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	c3a9c478-15f3-418f-99b6-fbd068756dc8	2026-05-02 13:31:38.153	2026-05-02 13:31:38.153	2026-05-02 12:28:46.718	2026-05-02 13:31:38.153	957ee766-4825-4b2c-a8f0-a77d433ef0fd	Deploy smart contract on SCAI mainnet network and remix IDE \nYou can get SCAI Mainnet coins using faucet: https://faucet.securechain.ai \nAnd you can add SCAI Mainnet in your metamask from the faucet website itself.\nMore details about SCAI mainnet: https://chainlist.org/chain/34 \n\nDeployed in 0x00d92d44f886cb61c31FeD18Ab0AEE2e29fa5C07	https://github.com/c-pranav-sharma/Blockchain/blob/main/Week-1/Smart_Contracts/HelloWorld.sol	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
34eaa51b-576d-44bb-89dd-177c4e740baf	Final Project Selection	Choose one final project:\n\n NFT Marketplace, \nDeFi Staking Platform, \nToken Vesting System, \nMini DEX, \nDAO Governance Platform	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	2026-04-30 15:55:19.328	2026-04-30 15:55:19.328	2026-04-30 14:37:38.444	2026-04-30 15:55:19.328	82efb126-12c4-4cd2-a316-1b19ed8a987c	DeFi Staking Platform\n\nProject Overview\n\nFor the final blockchain project, I selected the DeFi Staking Platform. To make the project more innovative, I will develop it as a Smart Lock DeFi Staking Platform.\n\nSmartLock is a decentralized application that allows users to stake ERC-20 tokens and earn rewards through smart contracts. Unlike a basic staking platform, SmartLock will provide multiple staking plans with different lock periods and reward multipliers. Users can choose flexible staking or locked staking plans depending on how long they want to keep their tokens staked.\n\nThe main goal of this project is to create a more practical and realistic DeFi staking system where users are rewarded based on their commitment period. Longer staking durations will provide higher reward rates.\n\nReason for Choosing This Project\n\nI selected this project because staking is one of the most important use cases in decentralized finance. It helps users earn passive rewards by locking their tokens in a smart contract. This project also covers important blockchain concepts such as ERC-20 tokens, wallet connection, token approval, reward calculation, staking duration, smart contract security, and frontend integration.\n\nThe project is also suitable for full-stack blockchain development because it includes both smart contract logic and frontend Dapp development.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
a156616b-7286-4235-8f2a-87fd4b1cffc8	System Architecture Design	Design system architecture and smart contract logic. Prepare technical documentation and workflow diagrams	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	2026-04-30 17:02:32.145	2026-04-30 17:02:32.145	2026-04-30 15:15:22.958	2026-04-30 17:02:32.145	f24f6c81-2a83-490f-bfa5-a17f30a959f8	Project Requirements & Use Cases Report\n\nThe objective of this task is to define the complete requirements and use cases for the SmartLock DeFi Staking Platform. SmartLock is a decentralized staking application that allows users to stake ERC-20 tokens and earn rewards through smart contracts. Unlike a basic staking system, this platform provides different staking plans with lock periods and reward multipliers. The main idea of the project is that users who lock their tokens for a longer period will receive higher rewards.\n\nSmartLock will work as a blockchain-based decentralized application where users can connect their wallet, select a staking plan, stake tokens, earn rewards, and withdraw tokens. The platform will support different staking options such as a flexible plan, a silver plan, a gold plan, and a platinum plan. The flexible plan will have no lock period and will provide a normal reward rate. The silver plan will lock tokens for seven days and provide a higher reward multiplier. The gold plan will lock tokens for thirty days and provide an even better reward rate. The platinum plan will lock tokens for ninety days and provide the highest reward multiplier. This structure makes the platform more realistic and useful compared to a simple staking application.\n\nThe main users of the platform will be normal users or stakers who want to earn rewards by staking their tokens. These users will be able to connect their MetaMask wallet, check their token balance, choose a staking plan, approve the staking contract, stake tokens, view their pending rewards, claim rewards, and withdraw their tokens. Another important actor in the system is the admin or contract owner. The admin will manage the reward pool, pause the contract during emergency situations, unpause the contract when the issue is resolved, and maintain the platform. The smart contract will act as the core system that stores staking details, calculates rewards, applies lock period rules, transfers tokens, and enforces the logic of the platform. MetaMask will be used as the wallet provider to allow users to sign blockchain transactions.\n\nThe platform will have several functional requirements. Users must be able to connect their wallet and view their token balances. They must also be able to select a staking plan before staking tokens. Before staking, users will approve the smart contract to spend their ERC-20 tokens. After approval, users can stake tokens into their selected plan. The smart contract will record the amount staked, selected plan, staking start time, lock end time, and reward multiplier. Users should be able to view their staked amount, pending rewards, and lock period details from the frontend dashboard. The system should also allow users to claim rewards and withdraw tokens after the lock period is completed. If early withdrawal is allowed, the contract may apply a penalty when users withdraw before the lock period ends. The admin must be able to fund the reward pool and pause or unpause the contract when required.\n\nThe project also has several non-functional requirements. Security is one of the most important requirements because the smart contract will handle user funds. The contract should prevent common problems such as reentrancy attacks, incorrect reward calculation, unauthorized access, and invalid transactions. The reward calculation must be accurate and must depend on the amount staked, staking duration, and selected multiplier. The system should also be gas efficient so that users do not spend unnecessary transaction fees. The frontend should be simple and easy to use, so users can clearly understand how to stake, claim, and withdraw. The project code should be clean, organized, and easy to maintain. The system should also be testable using Hardhat so that all major contract functions can be verified before deployment.\n\nThe main use case of the platform begins when a user opens the SmartLock DApp and connects their MetaMask wallet. After the wallet is connected, the user can view the available staking plans and select one based on their preference. For example, a user who wants full flexibility can select the flexible plan, while a user who wants higher rewards can choose the gold or platinum plan. After selecting a plan, the user enters the staking amount and approves the staking contract to spend the tokens. Once approval is complete, the user confirms the staking transaction through MetaMask. The smart contract then transfers tokens from the user’s wallet to the staking contract and records all staking details.\n\nAnother important use case is reward tracking and claiming. After staking tokens, the user can visit the dashboard to view the pending rewards. The smart contract calculates rewards based on the staked amount, time passed, and multiplier of the selected plan. When the user clicks the claim button, MetaMask asks for transaction confirmation. After confirmation, the smart contract transfers the earned reward tokens to the user’s wallet and updates the reward information.\n\nThe withdrawal use case allows users to withdraw their staked tokens. If the selected lock period is completed, the user can withdraw tokens normally without penalty. If the user tries to withdraw before the lock period is over, the contract may apply an early withdrawal penalty. The remaining tokens are returned to the user, and the penalty amount can be kept inside the reward pool. This feature makes the project more realistic because many DeFi staking systems encourage users to keep tokens locked for a certain period.\n\nThe emergency withdrawal use case is included for safety. In this case, users can withdraw their staked tokens without claiming rewards. This function can be useful if there is an urgent issue or if the user wants to recover their staked tokens quickly. The smart contract will return the staked amount and reset the reward information for that staking position.\n\nThe admin use cases are also important for platform management. The admin will be able to fund the reward pool by transferring reward tokens into the staking contract. This ensures that the contract has enough tokens to pay user rewards. The admin can also pause the contract during emergency situations or maintenance. When the contract is paused, staking and withdrawal actions can be temporarily stopped. After the issue is resolved, the admin can unpause the contract and allow users to continue using the platform.\n\nThe smart contract will contain functions such as staking tokens, withdrawing tokens, claiming rewards, calculating earned rewards, viewing user staking positions, funding the reward pool, pausing the contract, unpausing the contract, and emergency withdrawal. The frontend will include a home page, wallet connection button, staking plan cards, staking form, dashboard, reward section, withdrawal section, admin panel, network warning, and transaction notifications. These features will allow users to interact with the blockchain in a simple and understandable way.\n\nThe overall workflow of the system is simple. A user opens the DApp, connects their wallet, selects a staking plan, approves tokens, and stakes tokens. After staking, the smart contract stores the staking details and starts calculating rewards. The user can later claim rewards or withdraw tokens. If the user withdraws after the lock period, the withdrawal happens normally. If the user withdraws early, the penalty logic may be applied. The admin maintains the platform by funding rewards and controlling emergency pause functions.\n\nThe SmartLock DeFi Staking Platform is inspired by existing DeFi staking systems, but it adds a plan-based staking model. Many DeFi platforms use staking to reward users for locking tokens and supporting the ecosystem. SmartLock improves the basic staking concept by adding flexible staking, locked staking, reward multipliers, early withdrawal penalty, and reward pool funding. This makes the project more practical and suitable as a final blockchain project.\n\nIn conclusion, the requirements and use cases of the SmartLock DeFi Staking Platform have been clearly defined. The platform will allow users to connect their wallet, choose a staking plan, stake ERC-20 tokens, earn rewards based on lock duration, claim rewards, and withdraw tokens. The project also includes admin features such as reward funding and emergency pause control. This task is now complete and the next task will be System Architecture Design.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
