c9fe45fb-06a2-402f-87a6-3ca2d6ecd41b	Smart Contract Development	Write and implement smart contracts for the selected final project	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	f3a3f301-69f7-4a16-a18d-5e54c307f7bc	2026-05-01 10:18:06.995	2026-05-01 10:18:06.995	2026-05-01 09:09:51.111	2026-05-01 10:18:06.995	5c976093-0014-40e1-b50e-228d0e65a684	SmartLock DeFi Staking Platform Smart Contracts\n\nProject Summary\nThis project implements the smart-contract layer for a DeFi staking platform using Solidity and Hardhat. The system includes:\n\n- A staking token for users: `SmartLockToken (SLT)`\n- A reward token for payouts: `SmartLockRewardToken (SLR)`\n- A staking contract: `SmartLockStaking`\n\nThe staking contract supports multiple staking plans with different lock durations and reward multipliers.\n\nCore Features Implemented\n- ERC-20 staking token contract\n- ERC-20 reward token contract\n- Staking with multiple plans\n- Reward accumulation over time\n- Reward claiming\n- Early withdrawal penalty for locked plans\n- Owner-funded reward pool\n- Pause and unpause controls\n- Emergency withdrawal flow\n- Read functions for plans, user stakes, and reward pool balance\n\nStaking Plans\n- Flexible: `0 days`, multiplier `1.0x`\n- Silver: `7 days`, multiplier `1.25x`\n- Gold: `30 days`, multiplier `1.5x`\n- Platinum: `90 days`, multiplier `2.0x`\n\nImprovements Made During Implementation\nThe original staking logic was strengthened to make it safer and more realistic for a final project submission.\n\n1. Reward Accrual Tracking\nRewards are now accrued into contract state using `unclaimedReward` per stake. This avoids losing pending rewards during contract interactions.\n\n2. Safer Withdrawals\nNormal withdrawals no longer depend on the reward pool having enough tokens at that exact moment. Users can still recover principal, and rewards remain claimable later once the reward pool is funded.\n\n3. Emergency Withdrawal Restriction\n`emergencyWithdraw` now works only when the contract is paused. This prevents users from bypassing the normal lock and penalty rules during standard operation.\n\n4. Automated Testing\nA complete Hardhat test file was added to verify:\n\n- deployment of staking plans\n- staking and claiming rewards\n- early withdrawal penalty behavior\n- withdrawal when reward pool is unfunded\n- emergency withdrawal while paused\n\nFiles Implemented / Updated\n- `contracts/SmartLockToken.sol`\n- `contracts/SmartLockRewardToken.sol`\n- `contracts/SmartLockStaking.sol`\n- `scripts/deploy.js`\n- `test/SmartLockStaking.js`\n- `hardhat.config.js`\n\nTools and Stack Used\n- Solidity `0.8.24`\n- Hardhat\n- OpenZeppelin Contracts\n- Ethers.js\n- Node.js\n\nExecution Steps\nInstall dependencies:\n\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\nCompile contracts:\n\n```bash\nnpm run compile\n```\n\nRun tests:\n\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\n\nStart a local blockchain:\n\n```bash\nnpx hardhat node\n```\n\nDeploy locally in another terminal:\n\n```bash\nnpm run deploy:local\n```\n\nTest Result\nAll automated tests passed:\n\n```text\n5 passing\n```\n\nLocal Deployment Result\nLatest successful local deployment addresses:\n\n- `SmartLockToken`: `0x5FC8d32690cc91D4c39d9d3abcBD16989F875707`\n- `SmartLockRewardToken`: `0x0165878A594ca255338adfa4d48449f69242Eb8F`\n- `SmartLockStaking`: `0xa513E6E4b8f2a923D98304ec87F64353C4D5C853`\n\nConclusion\nThis project delivers a working staking smart-contract system with deployment support and automated tests. It is suitable as a final academic project/demo, with improved contract behavior compared to the initial version.	https://github.com/xmx7hsgr2z-alt/smartlock-smart-contracts	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
