4eec5e9b-a5e0-4a82-b0ce-0ff6c0602491	Optimization + Conversion	Topics:\nA/B Testing (subject lines)\nFollow-up strategy (MOST IMPORTANT)\nClosing leads\nClient communication\n	6534e21c-9a7c-4a89-840b-28b102157ca0	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	6534e21c-9a7c-4a89-840b-28b102157ca0	2026-05-01 14:30:41.826	2026-05-01 14:30:41.826	2026-05-01 13:18:37.008	2026-05-01 14:30:41.827	aa8fe472-7eec-4791-83a3-dcc3286795db	Worked on executing A/B testing campaigns for email subject lines to analyze performance and optimize open rates. Implemented structured follow-up strategies to engage leads, ensuring timely reminders and value-based communication to improve response rates. Supported lead closing activities by providing accurate information, addressing client concerns, and coordinating next steps. Maintained effective client communication through emails and calls, shared campaign updates, handled client queries, and ensured a positive customer experience throughout the engagement process.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
c45bbd8a-b8da-4edc-a2e2-2ff421e3964f	System Architecture Design	Design system architecture and smart contract logic. Prepare technical documentation and workflow diagrams	597333b2-34f2-445c-a2fb-b85826155972	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	597333b2-34f2-445c-a2fb-b85826155972	2026-05-01 15:16:40.641	2026-05-01 15:16:40.641	2026-05-01 14:45:53.669	2026-05-01 15:16:40.641	f24f6c81-2a83-490f-bfa5-a17f30a959f8	System Architecture Design – NFT Marketplace\n\nOverview:\nThe NFT Marketplace is designed as a decentralized application (DApp) consisting of smart contracts for asset management and a frontend interface for user interaction. The system follows a modular architecture separating NFT creation and marketplace logic.\n\n---\n\nArchitecture Components:\n\n1. Smart Contracts Layer:\n\na) NFT Contract (ERC-721):\n\n* Implements ERC-721 standard using OpenZeppelin\n* Handles minting and ownership of NFTs\n* Stores token metadata (IPFS URI)\n\nb) Marketplace Contract:\n\n* Handles listing, buying, and cancellation of NFTs\n* Maintains listing data (price, seller)\n* Manages seller proceeds securely\n* Uses ReentrancyGuard and access control\n\n---\n\n2. Frontend Layer:\n\n* Built using React.js\n* Uses ethers.js for blockchain interaction\n* Allows users to:\n  • Connect wallet\n  • Mint NFTs\n  • List NFTs\n  • Buy NFTs\n  • View marketplace listings\n\n---\n\n3. Wallet Integration:\n\n* MetaMask or compatible wallet\n* Used for transaction signing and authentication\n\n---\n\n4. Storage Layer:\n\n* IPFS for storing NFT metadata and assets\n* Only metadata hash stored on-chain\n\n---\n\nSmart Contract Logic:\n\nData Structures:\n\n* Mapping for listings: NFT address → tokenId → listing details\n* Mapping for proceeds: seller address → earned balance\n\nCore Functions:\n\n* mintNFT() → Creates new NFT\n* listItem() → Lists NFT for sale after approval\n* buyItem() → Transfers NFT ownership upon payment\n* cancelListing() → Removes NFT from marketplace\n* withdrawProceeds() → Allows seller to withdraw funds\n\nSecurity Measures:\n\n* Reentrancy protection for financial functions\n* Ownership checks for listing and cancellation\n* Validation of price and existence of listings\n\n---\n\nWorkflow Diagram (Logical Flow):\n\n1. User connects wallet\n2. User mints NFT via NFT contract\n3. User approves marketplace contract\n4. User lists NFT with price\n5. Buyer selects NFT and sends payment\n6. Smart contract transfers NFT to buyer\n7. Seller balance updated\n8. Seller withdraws earnings\n\n---\n\nDeployment Architecture:\n\n* Smart contracts deployed using Foundry on EVM-compatible network\n* Frontend deployed on Vercel\n* RPC provider (Alchemy/Infura) for blockchain communication\n\n---\n\nThe architecture is fully EVM-compatible and can be deployed across networks such as Ethereum Sepolia and SCAI mainnet with minimal configuration changes.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
1bed0317-713b-4c82-9b68-7e92d1d3421e	Project Requirements & Use Cases	Understand the project requirements and use cases. Study similar existing protocols (NFT marketplaces, staking platforms, etc.)	597333b2-34f2-445c-a2fb-b85826155972	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	597333b2-34f2-445c-a2fb-b85826155972	2026-05-01 14:44:26.944	2026-05-01 14:44:26.944	2026-05-01 14:14:09.057	2026-05-01 14:44:26.944	7c1ce787-d304-4d76-bbf2-279ea0a2508c	Project Requirements & Use Cases – NFT Marketplace\n\nObjective:\nTo build a decentralized NFT marketplace where users can mint, list, buy, and sell NFTs securely using smart contracts without relying on intermediaries.\n\nCore Requirements:\n\n1. NFT Minting:\n   Users should be able to mint NFTs using the ERC-721 standard. Each NFT will represent a unique digital asset with metadata stored off-chain (e.g., IPFS).\n\n2. Listing NFTs:\n   NFT owners should be able to list their tokens for sale by specifying a price. The marketplace contract must verify ownership and approval before listing.\n\n3. Buying NFTs:\n   Users should be able to purchase listed NFTs by paying the specified price in the native blockchain currency. Ownership should be transferred securely upon successful payment.\n\n4. Cancel Listing:\n   Sellers should be able to cancel their listings anytime before the NFT is sold.\n\n5. Withdraw Proceeds:\n   Sellers should be able to withdraw their accumulated funds from successful sales.\n\n6. Security:\n   The contract should include protections against reentrancy attacks, unauthorized access, and invalid transactions.\n\n7. Events:\n   Emit events for key actions like listing, buying, and cancellation for frontend indexing.\n\n---\n\nUse Cases:\n\n1. Creator Minting NFTs:\n   A user creates and mints a new NFT representing digital art and becomes the owner.\n\n2. Seller Listing NFT:\n   The owner lists the NFT on the marketplace with a fixed price.\n\n3. Buyer Purchasing NFT:\n   Another user browses available NFTs and purchases one by sending the required payment.\n\n4. Seller Cancelling Listing:\n   The seller decides to remove the NFT from sale before it is purchased.\n\n5. Seller Withdrawing Earnings:\n   After a successful sale, the seller withdraws the earned funds from the contract.\n\n---\n\nReference Platforms Studied:\n• OpenSea – General NFT marketplace model\n• Blur – Efficient trading and marketplace UX\n• LooksRare – Decentralized reward-based marketplace\n\n---\n\nThe system is designed to be EVM-compatible and can be deployed on networks like Ethereum or SCAI mainnet.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
