f963872e-0612-415f-b8af-7cd989667172	Case Study 2:	Case Study 2:\n“CoinMask Token & Decentralized Ecosystem”\n	1aa78d53-b435-431c-b8eb-0a6b19e4c587	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	1aa78d53-b435-431c-b8eb-0a6b19e4c587	2026-05-05 11:35:04.376	2026-05-05 11:35:04.376	2026-05-05 11:33:50.025	2026-05-05 11:35:04.376	14640d49-5644-4ef5-892b-267512616ca4	Case Study 2:\n“CoinMask Token & Decentralized Ecosystem”\n\n\ncase study 2	https://github.com/Shreeyoshi-Goldar/week-3	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
5e0b3466-d2f7-4853-977b-ed2fc16a16d7	Smart Contract Development	Write and implement smart contracts for the selected final project	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-02 12:44:05.94	2026-05-02 12:44:05.94	2026-05-02 06:16:09.794	2026-05-02 12:44:05.94	5c976093-0014-40e1-b50e-228d0e65a684	1. DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT & DEPENDENCIES\nFramework: Hardhat (selected over Foundry for tighter integration with the React/Vite frontend testing workflow).\nNetwork: SCAI Testnet (deployment target for V1), SCAI Mainnet (Production).\nLibraries: OpenZeppelin Contracts v4.x.\n\nERC721URIStorage.sol: For standard non-fungible token mechanics and off-chain metadata (IPFS) linking.\n\nReentrancyGuard.sol: Critical for preventing cross-function race conditions during state/value transfers.\n\nCounters.sol: For secure, atomic increments of _tokenIds and _itemsSold.\n\n2. CONTRACT ARCHITECTURE: ProvenanceMarket.sol\nTo optimize gas and reduce contract approval complexity for users, the ERC-721 token and the Marketplace logic are combined into a monolithic contract.\n\nState Variables & Structs:\n\nSolidity\n// Using Counters for ID tracking\nusing Counters for Counters.Counter;\nCounters.Counter private _tokenIds;\nCounters.Counter private _itemsSold;\n\naddress payable owner; // Protocol deployer (for potential fee collection later)\nuint256 listingPrice = 0.001 ether; // Base listing fee in SCAI\n\nstruct MarketItem {\n    uint256 itemId;\n    address nftContract;\n    uint256 tokenId;\n    address payable seller;\n    address payable owner;\n    uint256 price;\n    bool sold;\n}\n\nmapping(uint256 => MarketItem) private idToMarketItem;\nEvents (Crucial for Frontend Indexing):\n\nSolidity\nevent MarketItemCreated(\n    uint256 indexed itemId,\n    address indexed nftContract,\n    uint256 indexed tokenId,\n    address seller,\n    address owner,\n    uint256 price,\n    bool sold\n);\n3. CORE WRITE FUNCTIONS (STATE MUTATION)\nA. createToken(string memory tokenURI, uint256 price)\n\nPurpose: Combines minting and listing into a single transaction to drastically reduce user friction and gas costs.\n\nExecution:\n\nIncrements _tokenIds.\n\nCalls _mint(msg.sender, newTokenId) and _setTokenURI(newTokenId, tokenURI).\n\nCalls internal createMarketItem function to transfer custody from the creator to the contract address and populate the idToMarketItem mapping.\n\nConstraint: Requires msg.value == listingPrice (if charging protocol fees) and price > 0.\n\nB. createMarketSale(address nftContract, uint256 itemId)\n\nPurpose: Facilitates the exchange of SCAI for the asset.\n\nSecurity: Must use the nonReentrant modifier. Must strictly follow the CEI (Checks-Effects-Interactions) pattern.\n\nExecution:\n\nSolidity\nfunction createMarketSale(address nftContract, uint256 itemId) public payable nonReentrant {\n    uint price = idToMarketItem[itemId].price;\n    uint tokenId = idToMarketItem[itemId].tokenId;\n    address seller = idToMarketItem[itemId].seller;\n\n    require(msg.value == price, "Please submit the asking price in order to complete the purchase");\n    require(msg.sender != seller, "Protocol Constraint: Cannot purchase your own listed asset."); // Hardcoded fix for the frontend bug\n\n    // Effects\n    idToMarketItem[itemId].owner = payable(msg.sender);\n    idToMarketItem[itemId].sold = true;\n    idToMarketItem[itemId].seller = payable(address(0));\n    _itemsSold.increment();\n\n    // Interactions\n    _transfer(address(this), msg.sender, tokenId);\n    payable(owner).transfer(listingPrice); // Transfer fee to protocol\n    payable(seller).transfer(msg.value); // Transfer funds to seller\n}\n4. CORE READ FUNCTIONS (RPC INDEXING)\nSince we are using direct RPC calls for the incognito/unauthenticated user flows, the contract needs robust view functions to return arrays of structs.\n\nfetchMarketItems(): Returns all unsold items. Iterates through _tokenIds, checks if idToMarketItem[i].owner == address(this).\n\nfetchMyNFTs(): Used for the Dashboard "Personal Holdings". Returns items where owner == msg.sender.\n\nfetchItemsListed(): Used for the Dashboard "Active Listings". Returns items where seller == msg.sender.\n\nOptimization Note: View functions cost no gas when called externally by the frontend, but iterating over large arrays on-chain can eventually exceed block gas limits if the protocol scales massively. For V1, this array iteration is acceptable. For V2, we will need to implement a dedicated subgraph (The Graph).\n\n5. SECURITY & AUDIT CHECKLIST\n[x] Reentrancy: nonReentrant modifier applied to createMarketSale.\n\n[x] Integer Overflow/Underflow: Mitigated natively by using Solidity ^0.8.0.\n\n[x] Access Control: msg.sender verified on all transfer executions. Self-buy prevention enforced on-chain.\n\n[x] Pull over Push: Currently using direct .transfer for simplicity in V1. Note to self: Consider refactoring to a withdrawal pattern (pull) for the seller funds in V2 if SCAI network introduces weird gas dynamics for smart contract wallets.\n\n6. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS\nWrite the ProvenanceMarket.sol contract in the /contracts directory.\n\nDraft Hardhat test scripts (test/market-test.js) using Chai. Specifically test the require(msg.sender != seller) failure case to ensure the exploit is patched.\n\nSpin up a local Hardhat node (npx hardhat node) and deploy locally.\n\nExtract the compiled JSON ABI from artifacts/contracts/... and import it directly into the React frontend's constants.js file so Wagmi can interact with it.	https://github.com/Krrish41/provenance-protocol	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
479833d7-e3c4-4a7f-baf1-fbf269f0925f	Frontend Integration (React + Web3)	Integrate frontend using React / Web3.js / Ethers.js with the smart contracts	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-02 13:30:56.807	2026-05-02 13:30:56.807	2026-05-02 06:16:08.509	2026-05-02 13:30:56.807	299f6332-d5b8-4cfb-975b-b9ae4cfb1d70	1. INTEGRATION ARCHITECTURE\nWhile older tutorials rely heavily on raw Web3.js or Ethers.js injected directly into React components, Provenance Protocol will utilize Wagmi v2 (powered by Viem) paired with RainbowKit. This provides a significantly more robust, react-native way to handle asynchronous blockchain state, caching, and wallet connection lifecycles without writing massive boilerplate contexts.\n\nThe Integration Bridge:\n\nABI (Application Binary Interface): The compiled JSON output from the Hardhat ProvenanceMarket.sol compilation. This acts as the translation manual between Javascript and Solidity.\n\nContract Address: The deployed 0x... address on the SCAI network.\n\nViem/Wagmi Hooks: Used to execute reads (RPC calls) and writes (wallet signatures) using the ABI and Address.\n\n2. PROVIDER CONFIGURATION (main.jsx / App.jsx)\nThe entire application must be wrapped in a specific provider tree to manage the global Web3 state and the fallback RPC discussed in Phase 02.\n\nJavaScript\nimport { WagmiProvider, createConfig, http } from 'wagmi';\nimport { scaiMainnet, scaiTestnet } from 'wagmi/chains'; // Assuming custom chain config if SCAI isn't default\nimport { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query';\nimport { RainbowKitProvider, darkTheme } from '@rainbow-me/rainbowkit';\n\n// Setup Query Client for caching RPC responses\nconst queryClient = new QueryClient();\n\n// Configure Wagmi\nconst config = createConfig({\n  chains: [scaiTestnet, scaiMainnet],\n  transports: {\n    // Injecting the Thirdweb RPC Fallback\n    [scaiMainnet.id]: http(import.meta.env.VITE_SCAI_RPC_URL), \n  },\n});\n\n// App Wrapper structure:\n// <WagmiProvider config={config}>\n//   <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>\n//     <RainbowKitProvider theme={customObsidianTheme}>\n//       <App />\n//     ...\n3. CORE HOOKS (STATE & MUTATION)\nInstead of manually instantiating new ethers.Contract(), we will use Wagmi's declarative hooks.\n\nA. Read Operations (Data Fetching for /explore)\n\nHook: useReadContract\n\nImplementation: Used to call fetchMarketItems().\n\nAdvantage: Automatically handles loading states (isLoading, isFetching) and caches the data. It also seamlessly uses the fallback RPC if the user's wallet is not connected (solving the Incognito bug).\n\nJavaScript\nconst { data: marketItems, isLoading, error } = useReadContract({\n  address: PROVENANCE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS,\n  abi: ProvenanceMarketABI,\n  functionName: 'fetchMarketItems',\n});\nB. Write Operations (Minting & Buying)\n\nHook: useWriteContract paired with useWaitForTransactionReceipt.\n\nImplementation:\n\n/mint: Calling createToken(tokenURI, price) after the Pinata IPFS upload succeeds.\n\n/explore: Calling createMarketSale(nftContract, itemId) when a user clicks "Buy Asset".\n\nValue Transfer: When calling createMarketSale, the value parameter must be explicitly parsed to Wei using Viem's parseEther.\n\nJavaScript\nimport { parseEther } from 'viem';\n\nconst { writeContract, data: hash } = useWriteContract();\n\nconst handleBuy = (item) => {\n  writeContract({\n    address: PROVENANCE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS,\n    abi: ProvenanceMarketABI,\n    functionName: 'createMarketSale',\n    args: [item.nftContract, item.itemId],\n    value: parseEther(item.price.toString()), // Converting UI SCAI to Wei\n  });\n};\n4. DATA PARSING & FORMATTING LOGIC\nSmart contracts return data in raw formats (BigInts for numbers, raw strings for URIs). The frontend must intercept and format this before rendering.\n\nBigInt to String/Number: Prices returned from the contract will be in Wei (e.g., 1000000000000000000). Use Viem's formatEther to convert this back to 1.0 SCAI for the UI.\n\nIPFS Interception: Map over the array returned by fetchMarketItems. For every item, extract the tokenURI, pass it through the resolveIPFS(uri) utility (pointing to the Pinata Gateway), fetch the resulting JSON metadata, and merge it with the contract data struct.\n\n5. ERROR HANDLING & UX LIFECYCLE\nBlockchain transactions are not instantaneous. The UI must reflect the exact state of the network.\n\nState 1: Idle. (Button reads "Buy Asset").\n\nState 2: Signature Pending. User clicked Buy. MetaMask pops up. (Button reads "Awaiting Signature...", UI disabled). Catch UserRejectedRequestError here if they close the modal.\n\nState 3: Mining (Tx Sent). Signature approved. Awaiting block confirmation. (Show custom Toast: "Transaction submitted to SCAI network. Mining...").\n\nState 4: Success/Fail. Receipt received. (Update UI to "Owned by You", trigger success Toast, invalidate React Query cache to automatically refresh the grid).\n\n6. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS (ENGINEERING)\nCopy the compiled ProvenanceMarket.json ABI from the Hardhat project into src/constants/abi.json.\n\nSet up the constants/index.js file to export the PROVENANCE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS securely.\n\nWrap the Vite root in the Wagmi, React Query, and RainbowKit providers.\n\nRefactor the static/mock data in the Explore component to use the useReadContract hook pointing to the deployed testnet contract.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
ec62cf32-a677-4bc4-9312-1f94cb344f42	Wallet Connection Integration	Connect wallet functionality (MetaMask, WalletConnect, Coinbase Wallet) to the DApp	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-02 14:07:37.775	2026-05-02 14:07:37.775	2026-05-02 06:16:07.91	2026-05-02 14:07:37.775	2a73a7a6-b539-4690-b3f4-814f234dc01e	1. ARCHITECTURAL OVERVIEW\nThe Provenance Protocol utilizes a modern Web3 onboarding stack to replace the fragmented "injected-only" connection methods of the past. By leveraging RainbowKit on top of Wagmi, the protocol ensures a seamless transition between mobile and desktop environments while maintaining the high-contrast Obsidian aesthetic.\n\nPrimary Library: RainbowKit (UI Layer)\n\nProtocol Layer: Wagmi v2 (State Management)\n\nTransport Layer: Viem (Low-level RPC interaction)\n\nMulti-Wallet Support: MetaMask, WalletConnect, Base Account (Coinbase), and Rainbow.\n\n2. CONFIGURATION & PROVIDER SETUP\nTo prevent the "black screen" crashes and state corruption identified in previous testing, the connection provider must be initialized at the root of the application.\n\nChain Configuration: Explicitly define SCAI Mainnet and Testnet parameters.\n\nRPC Fallback: Use the Thirdweb RPC URL as the default transport to ensure unauthenticated users can still view the market data.\n\nTheme Integration: Pass a custom darkTheme object to the RainbowKitProvider that overrides default rounded corners and bold weights to match the project's technical monospace style.\n\n3. CONNECTION WORKFLOWS\nA. The "Auth Guard" Logic\nThe frontend must strictly gate certain functionalities based on the connection state provided by the useAccount hook.\n\nDashboard: If !isConnected, the UI renders an "Authentication Required" placeholder instead of attempting to fetch empty personal holdings.\n\nMinting: Form inputs and the "Mint & List" button are hard-disabled until a valid signer is detected.\n\nB. Transaction Flow Handling\n\nRequest: User initiates a transaction (e.g., buying the Genesis Fragment // SV-01).\n\nSignature State: Monitor the useWriteContract status.\n\nError Catching: Wrap the connection logic in try/catch blocks to specifically handle UserRejectedRequestError. This prevents the app from hanging or crashing if a user closes the wallet popup without signing.\n\n4. MOBILE-SPECIFIC OPTIMIZATIONS\nGiven the "crowded" nature of mobile Web3 headers, the connection UI follows these responsive rules:\n\nDynamic Visibility: On viewports under 768px, the primary "Connect Wallet" button is moved from the header row into the hamburger navigation menu to preserve logo spacing.\n\nCoarse Pointer Handling: Detect touch devices to disable custom pointer/dot effects that often get "stuck" when a user taps the screen.\n\nWalletConnect Modal: Ensure the projectId is correctly configured in Wagmi to trigger deep-linking for mobile wallets (MetaMask Mobile, Coinbase Wallet App).\n\n5. SECURITY & SESSION PERSISTENCE\nAuto-Connect: Enable the reconnectOnMount feature in Wagmi to maintain sessions across page refreshes.\n\nSanitization: All addresses retrieved from useAccount are treated as untrusted inputs. Use checksummed addresses for on-chain queries.\n\nPrivacy: Ensure no sensitive wallet metadata or transaction history is logged to external analytics or Vercel runtime logs.\n\n6. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS\nVerify the projectId from WalletConnect Cloud is active and added to the .env file.\n\nApply the whitespace-nowrap and text-xs CSS fixes to the mobile navbar button to prevent text-wrapping bugs.\n\nTest the "Connection Termination" flow (closing the modal mid-process) to ensure the React Error Boundary catches the rejection.\n\nStandardize all button text to "Connect Wallet" for UI consistency.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
bc90a6dd-c6e2-4396-b346-7fbc41d198e3	Blockchain Network & API Integration	Integrate blockchain network and APIs for full DApp functionality	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-02 14:39:12.925	2026-05-02 14:39:12.925	2026-05-02 06:16:06.883	2026-05-02 14:39:12.925	a912274c-d460-4a5b-9a91-6c101d9edbaa	1. NETWORK TOPOLOGY (SCAI MAINNET)The protocol interacts with the SCAI Mainnet using a hybrid provider strategy to balance performance for guest users with secure write-access for authenticated holders.Primary RPC Provider: [https://34.rpc.thirdweb.com](https://34.rpc.thirdweb.com). This is utilized as the global fallback for all "read" operations, ensuring the marketplace loads instantly even in incognito mode or before a wallet is connected.Injected Provider: Utilized for all state-changing transactions (Minting, Buying, Listing). The app dynamically switches to the user's wallet provider (MetaMask, Rainbow) once a session is established.Chain Configuration: Integrated via Wagmi chains configuration to enforce correct network switching if a user is on an unsupported chain (e.g., Ethereum Mainnet).2. STORAGE ARCHITECTURE (PINATA IPFS API)Data that is too heavy for on-chain storage (images, metadata JSONs) is offloaded to the InterPlanetary File System via Pinata.Upload API (The Write Path): Uses the Pinata JWT for authenticated POST requests during the minting flow.Step 1: Upload raw media file -> Receive CID.Step 2: Construct Metadata JSON including the media CID.Step 3: Upload JSON -> Receive tokenURI for the smart contract.Gateway API (The Read Path): Employs a dedicated Pinata Gateway (salmon-blank-leopon-846.mypinata.cloud) to bypass the severe rate-limiting of public IPFS nodes.Security: API keys and JWTs are managed via Vercel Environment Variables (VITE_PINATA_JWT) to prevent exposure in the client-side source code.3. API INTEGRATION WORKFLOWThe integration logic follows a strict "ceaseless synchronization" pattern to ensure the UI remains reactive to blockchain events.TriggerAPI/Network ActionPurposePage LoadfetchMarketItems (via RPC)Populates the Explore page using the Thirdweb fallback.Form SubmitpinFileToIPFS (via Pinata)Immutably stores asset media before minting.SignatureuseWriteContract (via Wagmi)Triggers the wallet extension for transaction approval.Tx ConfirmationuseWaitForTransactionReceiptTriggers UI cache invalidation to refresh the marketplace.4. ERROR HANDLING & DETECTION LOGICTo resolve the specific UI bugs identified in testing, the API integration now includes active environment checks.Extension Detection: Before attempting a connection, the app checks for the presence of window.ethereum or specific wallet flags.Installation Redirects: If a user selects a wallet (e.g., Rainbow) and the API detection fails, the UI intercepts the "blank screen" state and serves a direct download link (rainbow.me/download/) instead.Rejection Catching: All API calls to the wallet are wrapped in try/catch blocks to handle UserRejectedRequestError without crashing the React DOM.5. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS[ ] Verify the VITE_SCAI_RPC_URL is correctly mapped in the production Vercel dashboard.[ ] Finalize the resolveIPFS utility to prepend the dedicated Pinata gateway URL to all CIDs.[ ] Test the RPC fallback speed in a "clean" incognito window to ensure load times remain under 3 seconds.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
