ce255a5b-5d74-4a7d-a9c8-844215d09233	Smart Contract Unit Testing	Perform unit testing of smart contracts using Hardhat / Foundry	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-03 01:33:27.082	2026-05-03 01:33:27.082	2026-05-02 06:16:01.834	2026-05-03 01:33:27.082	4935d097-17ab-4802-9415-2c9eaa7ef712	1. TESTING ENVIRONMENT SETUP\nFramework: Hardhat (Local Network)\n\nAssertion Library: Chai (via @nomicfoundation/hardhat-chai-matchers)\n\nTesting Accounts: Hardhat provides 20 local signers (Deployer, Buyer, Seller, etc.).\n\nCommand: npx hardhat test\n\n2. CORE TEST SUITES (test/market-test.js)\nA. Deployment & Initialization\n\nShould deploy successfully and assign the correct owner address.\n\nShould set the correct default listingPrice (e.g., 0.001 ether).\n\nB. Minting (createToken)\n\nShould increment the token ID and assign it to the contract address.\n\nShould correctly map the IPFS tokenURI.\n\nShould emit the MarketItemCreated event with correct struct data.\n\nShould fail if msg.value does not equal the protocol listing fee.\n\nC. Purchasing (createMarketSale)\n\nShould transfer the exact SCAI value to the seller.\n\nShould transfer the protocol fee to the contract owner.\n\nShould transfer the NFT custody from the contract to the buyer.\n\nShould update the sold boolean to true in the MarketItem mapping.\n\nShould emit the MarketItemSold event.\n\n3. SECURITY & EDGE CASES (CRITICAL)\nSelf-Buy Prevention (Bug Fix Verify):\n\nTest: Connect as User A -> Mint Asset -> User A attempts to call createMarketSale.\n\nAssertion: await expect(...).to.be.revertedWith("Protocol Constraint: Cannot purchase your own listed asset.")\n\nInsufficient Funds:\n\nTest: Buyer attempts to purchase with msg.value less than price.\n\nAssertion: Must revert.\n\nDouble Spend / Already Sold:\n\nTest: Buyer B attempts to purchase an asset immediately after Buyer A.\n\nAssertion: Must revert (item no longer exists in active mapping or is owned by Buyer A).\n\n4. ACTION ITEMS\nWrite the initial deployment setup block inside describe("ProvenanceMarket", function () { ... }) using Hardhat's loadFixture for faster test execution.\n\nDraft the "Self-Buy" edge case first to verify the previous patch.\n\nRun npx hardhat coverage to ensure 100% path coverage on state-mutating functions before SCAI Testnet deployment.	https://github.com/Krrish41/provenance-protocol	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
