3b77b7d9-412f-4cd3-8aef-793be0da8ef1	Documentation & Demo Video	Deliverables: \n● Live project link on Vercel.com  \n● Github public repository of the project with documentation in readme and code.\n	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	2026-05-03 15:57:45.193	2026-05-03 15:57:45.193	2026-05-02 06:15:58.524	2026-05-03 15:57:45.193	9b89eb58-25fe-45ae-919c-fe53b06dce0d	Please find the complete technical documentation and source code for the Provenance Protocol in the GitHub repository linked below. The repository's README serves as the comprehensive technical guide to the project's architecture.\n\nDocumentation Highlights Included in the Repository:\n\nSmart Contract Architecture: Details on the ProvenanceMarketplace.sol deployment on the SCAI Mainnet, including transaction payload construction and contract verification.\n\nMobile Routing Engine: Full breakdown of the synchronous Universal Link trigger system engineered to bypass mobile browser sandbox restrictions for flawless wallet handoffs.\n\nWeb3 State Management: Explanation of the Wagmi and Viem implementation, in-app browser auto-synchronization, and resilient data pipelines using Promise.allSettled for IPFS metadata.\n\nUI/UX Design System: Overview of the custom Obsidian and Cyber-Lime styling, including the strict z-index stacking contexts used for complex, cross-platform overlay management.\n\nProject Demo Note:\nPlease note that I have intentionally opted not to provide a standard screen-recorded demo video. The core engineering achievement of this application—solving Web3 mobile fragmentation via seamless OS-level wallet handoffs and synchronous deep-linking—cannot be accurately captured or evaluated through a flat video.\n\nTo properly review the technical architecture and user experience, please interact with the live deployment directly. I highly encourage reviewers to open the Vercel link below on a mobile device to experience the native wallet routing and auto-synchronization firsthand.	https://github.com/Krrish41/provenance-protocol	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
