c25eb53f-db01-47b9-afea-e55143b6b6b7	Smart Contract Development	Write and implement smart contracts for the selected final project	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	2026-05-05 05:26:14.681	2026-05-05 05:26:14.682	2026-05-04 17:47:16.246	2026-05-05 05:26:14.682	5c976093-0014-40e1-b50e-228d0e65a684	In this phase, I designed and implemented the smart contracts that form the core logic of the DAO Governance Platform using Solidity and OpenZeppelin libraries.\n\nThe system consists of multiple contracts working together to handle governance:\n\n1. GovernanceToken.sol:\nAn ERC20Votes-based token that provides voting power to users. It uses snapshot functionality to ensure fair voting by locking voting power at the time a proposal is created.\n\n2. GovernorContract.sol:\nImplements the governance logic using OpenZeppelin Governor framework. It manages:\n- Proposal creation\n- Voting mechanism\n- Quorum validation\n- Proposal state transitions (Pending, Active, Succeeded, Executed)\n\n3. Timelock.sol:\nActs as a security layer by introducing a delay before executing approved proposals. This prevents immediate execution and allows time for review.\n\n4. Box.sol:\nA sample target contract used to demonstrate execution of governance decisions. Approved proposals can trigger state changes in this contract.\n\nAdditionally, a simplified contract (SimpleDAO.sol) was developed for learning and testing core concepts such as proposal storage and vote tracking.\n\nKey Functionalities Implemented:\n- Token-based voting using ERC20Votes\n- Snapshot mechanism to prevent vote manipulation\n- Prevention of double voting\n- Proposal lifecycle management\n- Timelock-based execution flow\n\nTesting:\nUnit tests were written using Hardhat to validate proposal creation, voting behavior, and execution logic, including edge cases.\n\nThis implementation ensures a secure, modular, and industry-aligned governance system similar to protocols like Compound.	https://github.com/jahnaviyakkala/dao-governance	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
