2ad043c6-d340-40bc-910a-bc5feb4a4f60	Blockchain fundamentals & Ethereum basics 	Blockchain fundamentals & Ethereum basics 	87aa518d-c5b1-4644-8770-bfed12e00640	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	87aa518d-c5b1-4644-8770-bfed12e00640	2026-05-06 08:48:55.862	2026-05-06 08:48:55.862	2026-05-06 06:10:17.688	2026-05-06 08:48:55.862	2ba371fd-2faa-4e2b-a786-b040566ff81d	Blockchain Fundamentals & Ethereum Basics — Work Notes\n\n1. Blockchain Fundamentals\n\nDefinition\nA blockchain is a decentralized, distributed digital ledger used to record transactions across multiple nodes securely and transparently.\n\nStructure of a Block\nEach block contains:\n\n* Transaction Data\n* Hash (unique identifier)\n* Previous Block Hash\n\nBlocks are linked together forming a chain\n\nKey Characteristics\n\n* Decentralization: No central authority\n* Immutability: Data cannot be altered once added\n* Transparency: All participants can view transactions\n* Security: Uses cryptographic hashing\n\nWorking Process\n\n1. Transaction is initiated\n2. Broadcast to network\n3. Nodes validate transaction\n4. Block is created\n5. Block added to chain\n6. Transaction completed\n\nConsensus Mechanisms\n\n* Proof of Work (PoW)\n  Requires computational power (mining)\n  Used by Bitcoin\n\n* Proof of Stake (PoS)\n  Validators stake cryptocurrency\n  Used by Ethereum (current)\n\nApplications\n\n* Cryptocurrencies\n* Supply chain management\n* Voting systems\n* Digital identity\n* Healthcare records\n\n2. Ethereum Basics\n\nDefinition\nEthereum is a blockchain platform that enables the development of decentralized applications (dApps) using smart contracts.\n\nSmart Contracts\n\n* Self-executing programs stored on blockchain\n* Automatically execute when conditions are met\n\nExample\nIF payment received → transfer ownership\n\nEthereum Virtual Machine (EVM)\n\n* Executes smart contracts\n* Runs on all Ethereum nodes\n* Ensures consistent output across the network\n\nEther (ETH)\n\n* Native cryptocurrency of Ethereum\n* Used for:\n  Transaction fees\n  Smart contract execution\n\nGas Fees\n\n* Fee required to perform operations\n* Prevents network abuse\n* Paid in ETH\n\nEthereum Evolution\n\n* Earlier: Proof of Work\n* Now: Proof of Stake\n\nAdvantages\n\n* Lower energy consumption\n* Better scalability\n* Improved efficiency\n\nUse Cases of Ethereum\n\n* Decentralized Finance (DeFi)\n* Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs)\n* Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs)\n* Gaming and marketplaces\n\n3. Key Difference\n\nFeature        Blockchain              Ethereum\nPurpose        Record transactions     Build decentralized apps\nFlexibility    Limited                 Highly programmable\nNative Token   Varies                  Ether (ETH)\n\n4. Summary\n   Blockchain provides a secure, decentralized ledger\n   Ethereum extends blockchain with programmability\n   Smart contracts enable automation without intermediaries\n\n5. Next Learning Steps\n   Learn Solidity (Ethereum programming language)\n   Practice writing smart contracts\n   Use tools like Remix IDE / Hardhat\n   Build a simple dApp	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
