734bb8b2-031e-4530-9db6-010266e77432	System Architecture Design	Design system architecture and smart contract logic. Prepare technical documentation and workflow diagrams	da5bdc0e-ba05-4e65-b9d3-a94e96d2e06d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	da5bdc0e-ba05-4e65-b9d3-a94e96d2e06d	2026-05-07 10:33:42.591	2026-05-07 10:33:42.592	2026-05-06 17:31:43.752	2026-05-07 10:33:42.592	f24f6c81-2a83-490f-bfa5-a17f30a959f8	## system overview\n\nThe application follows a decentralized architecture where users interact directly with smart contracts through a frontend interface connected via wallet providers.\n\n## architecture flow\n\nUser Wallet\n↓\nFrontend Application\n↓\nSmart Contract Layer\n↓\nERC20 Token Transfers\n\n## frontend layer\n\nThe frontend is responsible for:\n\n* Wallet connection\n* Displaying vesting schedules\n* Allowing beneficiaries to claim tokens\n* Admin creation of vesting schedules\n\n## smart contract layer\n\nThe smart contract manages:\n\n* Vesting schedule creation\n* Token release calculations\n* Claim validation\n* Cliff and duration tracking\n* Beneficiary ownership\n\n## blockchain layer\n\nThe application is deployed on the Ethereum Sepolia Testnet for development and testing purposes.\n\n## contract structure\n\nMain Contract:\n\n* TokenVesting.sol\n\nCore Functions:\n\n* createVesting()\n* claim()\n* releasableAmount()\n* revoke()\n\n## security considerations\n\n* Access control validation\n* Reentrancy protection\n* Safe token transfers\n* Timestamp validation\n* Input parameter checks\n\n## development approach\n\nThe project is being developed incrementally:\n\n1. Architecture planning\n2. Smart contract development\n3. Frontend integration\n4. Testing and optimization\n5. Deployment and documentation	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
cf89df3e-4b80-41c1-bbdd-fbe3b86a776e	Project Requirements & Use Cases	Understand the project requirements and use cases. Study similar existing protocols (NFT marketplaces, staking platforms, etc.)	da5bdc0e-ba05-4e65-b9d3-a94e96d2e06d	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	da5bdc0e-ba05-4e65-b9d3-a94e96d2e06d	2026-05-07 11:22:12.92	2026-05-07 11:22:12.92	2026-05-06 17:28:16.219	2026-05-07 11:22:12.92	7c1ce787-d304-4d76-bbf2-279ea0a2508c	## objective\n\nThe goal of this project is to build a decentralized token vesting system that allows teams and organizations to distribute tokens securely over time using smart contracts.\n\n## problem statement\n\nMany blockchain projects require structured token distribution for team members, advisors, investors, and contributors. Manual token distribution lacks transparency and increases operational risk. A token vesting system automates this process using programmable smart contracts.\n\n## target users\n\n* Web3 startups\n* DAO organizations\n* Investors and advisors\n* Community contributors\n* Blockchain development teams\n\n## core features\n\n* Create vesting schedules\n* Support cliff periods\n* Linear token unlocking\n* Beneficiary token claiming\n* Admin management controls\n* Vesting dashboard interface\n\n## use cases\n\n* Team token allocation\n* Investor lockup schedules\n* Advisor vesting plans\n* Ecosystem reward distribution\n* Community incentive programs\n\n## technical goals\n\n* Secure smart contract implementation\n* Transparent on-chain transactions\n* Simple frontend interaction\n* Wallet integration support\n* Gas-efficient contract functions\n\n## planned technology stack\n\nFrontend:\n\n* Next.js\n* TailwindCSS\n* Wagmi\n* Viem\n* RainbowKit\n\nBlockchain:\n\n* Solidity\n* OpenZeppelin Contracts\n* Sepolia Testnet\n\nDevelopment Tools:\n\n* Hardhat\n* MetaMask\n* Etherscan	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
