1731d808-41a9-4003-ac8d-d2d85dc3d691	Fundamentals of Marketing Analytics	What is Marketing Analytics?\nKey Metrics:\nTraffic (Users, Sessions)\nCTR (Click Through Rate)\nConversion Rate\nBounce Rate\n	566054ee-7a45-451c-acd0-c38323030f39	\N	completed	medium	\N	\N	intern	566054ee-7a45-451c-acd0-c38323030f39	2026-05-07 18:55:08.949	2026-05-07 18:55:08.949	2026-05-07 13:17:02.567	2026-05-07 18:55:08.949	30ca7323-fa0b-4c21-8fd3-c30f9302fa0c	The Purpose & Value of Marketing Analytics\nThe Core Definition\nMarketing analytics replaces guesswork with hard facts. It is the process of using data to understand why things happen and what actions to take next, rather than just reporting on what happened.\n\n1. Maximized ROI (Stops Wasting Money)\nThe Problem: Spending money across multiple channels without knowing which one actually generates sales.\n\nThe Solution: Analytics attributes sales to specific campaigns.\n\nThe Action: Cut funding to underperforming channels and reallocate the budget to the top performers to instantly increase efficiency.\n\n2. Data-Driven Decisions (Ends "Gut Feeling" Debates)\nThe Problem: Relying on internal opinions (e.g., "I think customers want X").\n\nThe Solution: Letting user behavior dictate decisions.\n\nThe Action: A/B test different variables (colors, headlines, offers) and let the raw data prove exactly what the audience prefers.\n\n3. Mapping the Customer Journey\nThe Problem: Treating a purchase as a single event rather than a multi-step process.\n\nThe Solution: Tracking the entire path—from the first ad click, to browsing, to cart abandonment, to final purchase.\n\nThe Action: Identify the exact "leaks" in the funnel (e.g., where users drop off) and fix those specific bottlenecks to retain more potential buyers.\n\n4. Predictable Scaling\nThe Problem: Inability to reliably grow revenue without blindly throwing money at ads.\n\nThe Solution: establishing a baseline mathematical formula for customer acquisition (e.g., $X spend = Y traffic = Z sales).\n\nThe Action: Once the formula is proven and profitable, you can confidently scale up ad spend knowing the machine will produce a predictable outcome.Core Metrics\nTraffic (Users/Sessions): Ignore vanity volume. Focus 100% on identifying and scaling your high-intent sources (the channels that bring in actual buyers, not just window shoppers).\n\nCTR (Click-Through Rate): If CTR is low, fix the hook. 80% of ad success comes from the headline, image, or the first 3 seconds of a video.\n\nConversion Rate: Focus on removing friction. Make the desired action (buying, signing up) as easy and seamless as possible. Fix slow load times and confusing buttons.\n\nBounce Rate: Fix message match. The landing page must instantly deliver exactly what the ad or link promised, or the user will immediately leave.	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N
