d2414a92-afff-44dd-8eb7-b569b1a027d0	1e971923-3f5c-4873-a2bd-0d82b39cb0f1	cee30f5d-bb98-456a-8c27-d9b74b76dcae	task	2026-05-01 14:45:31.447	2026-05-01 15:15:49.462	30	The architecture contain two layers : a Solidity smart contract layer and  a React-based frontend layer ,\nFor the smart contract ,design a Tokenvesting.sol contract with a  VestingSchedule struct storing  totalAmount ,startTime , cliffDuration ,vesting duration ,amountClaimed ,and revoked status . key functions include creteVestingSchedule() ,claim(),vestedAmount(),claimableAmount(),revoke(),Access control is handled via OpenZeppenlin's Ownable.Events - VestingCreated , TokensClaimed,and VestingRevoked - are emitted for all state changes. For the frontend ,designed a React application with separate Admin and Beneficiary panels . The Admin Panel allows creating vesting schedules by inputting beneficiary address ,token amount ,cliff days and vesting duration . The Beneficiary panel displays a vesting progress bar, total allocated ,vested so fat , and a Claim button .\nWallet connection is handled via MetaMask using Ether.js BrowserProvider.The final Workflow is : Admin  deploys contract -> transfers ERC-20 tokens into contract-> creates schedules for beneficiaries -> beneficiaries connect Wallet ->view claimable balance -> call claim() to receive tokens . Prepared technical documentation covering contract ABI ,function signatures ,and data flow diagrams . Deployment target is semolina testate using Hardhat	2026-05-01 20:15:31.447959
