77bc2bdc-14a1-41b1-bca6-96d59a425763	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	5f76e1eb-3e4f-4ca2-98e1-6ceee99cd518	task	2026-05-02 06:16:11.744	2026-05-02 11:35:36.132	319	1. PROTOCOL DEFINITION & VISION\nObjective: Develop and deploy a non-custodial, high-performance decentralized application (dApp) on the SCAI Mainnet. The protocol facilitates the tokenization, verification, and exchange of digital assets with a strict emphasis on cryptographically verified history (provenance).\nTarget Architecture: React.js / Vite SPA frontend, IPFS decentralised storage, Web3 Provider (RainbowKit/Wagmi), deployed via Vercel.\nAesthetic Standard: Enterprise-grade engineering interface. High contrast (Obsidian, Cyber-Lime, Deep Steel), glassmorphic overlays, zero reliance on stock UI components.\n\n2. SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS\nA. Functional Requirements (Smart Contract & Frontend)\n\nAuthentication: Multi-wallet support (MetaMask, WalletConnect, Base) integrated via custom-themed RainbowKit modal.\n\nAsset Tokenization (Minting): Ability to upload media (max 10MB) to IPFS via Pinata gateway, generate metadata JSON, and mint ERC-721/equivalent tokens to the SCAI Mainnet.\n\nMarketplace Mechanics:\n\nList owned assets for sale at a defined SCAI price.\n\nExecute purchase transactions transferring asset ownership and settling SCAI balances securely.\n\nPrevent self-purchasing of listed assets via frontend logic and contract constraints.\n\nData Fetching: Hybrid data retrieval using injected wallet providers for authenticated users, and public RPC fallback providers for unauthenticated (incognito/guest) exploration.\n\nMedia Resolution: Automated detection and parsing of ipfs:// URIs through highly available public HTTP gateways to prevent broken image renders.\n\nB. Non-Functional Requirements\n\nRouting: Seamless SPA client-side routing configured via vercel.json to prevent 404s on direct URL access or refresh.\n\nLatency & Rendering: Maintain high frame rates for 3D particle background environments during DOM repaints and modal expansions.\n\nLegal Compliance: Visible, accessible Web3-standard Terms of Service and Privacy Policy outlining non-custodial risks and immutable data structures.\n\n3. CORE USE CASES (USER FLOWS)\nUC-01: Unauthenticated Exploration (The "Incognito" Flow)\n\nActor: Guest User / Recruiter.\n\nAction: Navigates to /explore.\n\nSystem Response: Utilizes public RPC fallback to fetch mainnet data. Displays the marketplace grid (e.g., Genesis Fragment // SV-01).\n\nConstraint: "Buy" or "List" buttons are replaced with "Connect Wallet" triggers.\n\nUC-02: Asset Origination (The "Mint" Flow)\n\nActor: Authenticated Creator.\n\nAction: Navigates to /mint. Uploads file, inputs Asset Name, Description, and Price. Signs transaction.\n\nSystem Response: Uploads to IPFS, executes mintAndList smart contract function. Notifies user via custom themed toast notification. Asset appears in Dashboard.\n\nUC-03: Secondary Market Acquisition (The "Buy" Flow)\n\nActor: Authenticated Collector.\n\nAction: Clicks an active listing on the Explore page. Modal expands containing asset provenance data. Clicks "Buy Asset".\n\nSystem Response: Frontend verifies the actor is not the current owner. Prompts wallet signature for the exact SCAI value. Upon block confirmation, updates UI to reflect new ownership.\n\n4. COMPARATIVE PROTOCOL ANALYSIS\nTo ensure Provenance Protocol meets industry standards, the following architectures were analyzed:\n\nA. OpenSea (The Standard Indexer)\n\nStrengths: Massive liquidity, highly standardized metadata handling across varied contract types.\n\nWeaknesses: Cluttered UI, slow IPFS resolution for obscure collections, frequent reliance on centralized caching.\n\nTakeaway for Provenance: Implement aggressive, multi-gateway IPFS resolution (resolveIPFS utility) to ensure media assets load faster and more reliably than standard indexers.\n\nB. Blur.io (The High-Frequency Interface)\n\nStrengths: Pro-trader aesthetic, keyboard shortcuts, rapid sweep functionalities, dark-mode default.\n\nWeaknesses: Steep learning curve, lacks emphasis on the "art" or visual asset itself.\n\nTakeaway for Provenance: Adopt the low-latency, technical aesthetic (Obsidian/Cyber-Lime palette, strict monospace typography). Ensure the UI feels like a financial terminal rather than a social media feed.\n\nC. Foundation / SuperRare (The Provenance Curators)\n\nStrengths: Beautiful, distraction-free UI. Heavy emphasis on creator history and the authentic "origin" of the piece.\n\nWeaknesses: High gas overhead for bespoke contracts, restrictive entry.\n\nTakeaway for Provenance: The detailed modal expansions and glassmorphic UI elements should mirror this premium feel. The asset descriptions (e.g., verifiable history from block zero) must be front and center to justify the protocol's namesake.\n\n5. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS\nFinalize and lock the custom RainbowKit theme parameters.\n\nDeploy the resolveIPFS utility across all image components.\n\nImplement the Dashboard Auth-Guard state logic.\n\nScrub remaining generic/stock UI elements (alerts, standard button hovers) and replace with custom components.	2026-05-02 11:46:11.74539
