ab359214-abbd-42f7-b516-3d41a82aed31	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	f6f9e504-77f2-4834-bf5b-1e7e6fe9ffeb	task	2026-05-02 11:35:37.775	2026-05-02 12:11:34.248	35	Implementation Plan: Optimization, Auth Guards, & UI Polish\nProposed Changes\n1. Market Loading Optimization (Speed & Pre-fetching)\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/pages/Explore.jsx\nExtract the RPC provider and contract instantiation outside of the React component so it's ready immediately.\nIntegrate @tanstack/react-query using the useQuery hook to fetch and cache market items.\nSet a staleTime of 1-5 minutes to prevent redundant RPC calls and eliminate the "Synchronizing" loader when navigating back to the Explore page.\n2. Strict Mint Page Auth Guard\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/pages/Mint.jsx\nImport useAccount from wagmi and ConnectButton from RainbowKit.\nAdd an authentication guard: If !isConnected, intercept the render and display a highly aesthetic, centered glassmorphic container identical to the Dashboard's guard.\nPrompt: "Authentication Required: Please connect your wallet to mint and list new assets."\n3. Button Consistency & Hover Contrast\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/components/layout/Navbar.jsx\nReplace the standard <ConnectButton /> with <ConnectButton.Custom> to tightly control the styling.\nApply the .btn-primary class to the Navbar connect button and ensure the text is exactly "Connect Wallet" with no variations.\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx\nUpdate the Connect button text in the unauthenticated state from "Connect Provenance Wallet" to exactly "Connect Wallet".\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/index.css\nEnsure the .btn-primary :hover state explicitly forces high contrast (background-color: #66FCF1, color: #0B0C10, with a glowing shadow) as defined, overriding any conflicting browser/tailwind defaults.\n4. Wallet Modal Crash (Error Handling)\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/components/ui/NFTCard.jsx\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/components/layout/Navbar.jsx\n[MODIFY] frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx\nWrap all invocations of RainbowKit's openConnectModal() in try/catch blocks.\nThis catches the UserRejectedRequestError thrown when a user closes the modal or rejects a connection mid-flight, preventing the unhandled promise rejection from bubbling up and crashing the React tree.\nVerification Plan\nExplore Speed: Navigate to Dashboard, then back to Explore. The assets should load instantly from cache without the skeleton loader.\nMint Guard: Disconnect the wallet and attempt to view the Mint page. It must show the locked state.\nButton Hover: Hover over the Connect Wallet buttons in the Navbar and Dashboard to verify the text turns solid Obsidian on a Cyber-Lime background.\nCrash Prevention: Attempt to connect, close the RainbowKit modal intentionally, and ensure the app does not crash to the Error Boundary or a black screen.	2026-05-02 17:05:37.776983
