f77cfe73-348a-4c8a-bdb5-195c05da242f	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	bc90a6dd-c6e2-4396-b346-7fbc41d198e3	task	2026-05-02 14:08:14.126	2026-05-02 14:39:12.916	30	1. NETWORK TOPOLOGY (SCAI MAINNET)The protocol interacts with the SCAI Mainnet using a hybrid provider strategy to balance performance for guest users with secure write-access for authenticated holders.Primary RPC Provider: [https://34.rpc.thirdweb.com](https://34.rpc.thirdweb.com). This is utilized as the global fallback for all "read" operations, ensuring the marketplace loads instantly even in incognito mode or before a wallet is connected.Injected Provider: Utilized for all state-changing transactions (Minting, Buying, Listing). The app dynamically switches to the user's wallet provider (MetaMask, Rainbow) once a session is established.Chain Configuration: Integrated via Wagmi chains configuration to enforce correct network switching if a user is on an unsupported chain (e.g., Ethereum Mainnet).2. STORAGE ARCHITECTURE (PINATA IPFS API)Data that is too heavy for on-chain storage (images, metadata JSONs) is offloaded to the InterPlanetary File System via Pinata.Upload API (The Write Path): Uses the Pinata JWT for authenticated POST requests during the minting flow.Step 1: Upload raw media file -> Receive CID.Step 2: Construct Metadata JSON including the media CID.Step 3: Upload JSON -> Receive tokenURI for the smart contract.Gateway API (The Read Path): Employs a dedicated Pinata Gateway (salmon-blank-leopon-846.mypinata.cloud) to bypass the severe rate-limiting of public IPFS nodes.Security: API keys and JWTs are managed via Vercel Environment Variables (VITE_PINATA_JWT) to prevent exposure in the client-side source code.3. API INTEGRATION WORKFLOWThe integration logic follows a strict "ceaseless synchronization" pattern to ensure the UI remains reactive to blockchain events.TriggerAPI/Network ActionPurposePage LoadfetchMarketItems (via RPC)Populates the Explore page using the Thirdweb fallback.Form SubmitpinFileToIPFS (via Pinata)Immutably stores asset media before minting.SignatureuseWriteContract (via Wagmi)Triggers the wallet extension for transaction approval.Tx ConfirmationuseWaitForTransactionReceiptTriggers UI cache invalidation to refresh the marketplace.4. ERROR HANDLING & DETECTION LOGICTo resolve the specific UI bugs identified in testing, the API integration now includes active environment checks.Extension Detection: Before attempting a connection, the app checks for the presence of window.ethereum or specific wallet flags.Installation Redirects: If a user selects a wallet (e.g., Rainbow) and the API detection fails, the UI intercepts the "blank screen" state and serves a direct download link (rainbow.me/download/) instead.Rejection Catching: All API calls to the wallet are wrapped in try/catch blocks to handle UserRejectedRequestError without crashing the React DOM.5. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS[ ] Verify the VITE_SCAI_RPC_URL is correctly mapped in the production Vercel dashboard.[ ] Finalize the resolveIPFS utility to prepend the dedicated Pinata gateway URL to all CIDs.[ ] Test the RPC fallback speed in a "clean" incognito window to ensure load times remain under 3 seconds.	2026-05-02 19:38:14.128018
a40a8fec-5743-4c06-a27f-8e115495f139	c3a9c478-15f3-418f-99b6-fbd068756dc8	7ad762b8-e746-40a4-947e-60b97ada52a1	task	2026-05-02 14:01:56.388	2026-05-02 14:03:23.22	1	Blockchain fundamentals & Ethereum basics \n\nDocumented basic understanding of the concepts	2026-05-02 19:31:56.389531
96cc0c56-88c3-4231-8e88-17126487455a	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	ec62cf32-a677-4bc4-9312-1f94cb344f42	task	2026-05-02 13:31:21.817	2026-05-02 14:07:37.764	36	1. ARCHITECTURAL OVERVIEW\nThe Provenance Protocol utilizes a modern Web3 onboarding stack to replace the fragmented "injected-only" connection methods of the past. By leveraging RainbowKit on top of Wagmi, the protocol ensures a seamless transition between mobile and desktop environments while maintaining the high-contrast Obsidian aesthetic.\n\nPrimary Library: RainbowKit (UI Layer)\n\nProtocol Layer: Wagmi v2 (State Management)\n\nTransport Layer: Viem (Low-level RPC interaction)\n\nMulti-Wallet Support: MetaMask, WalletConnect, Base Account (Coinbase), and Rainbow.\n\n2. CONFIGURATION & PROVIDER SETUP\nTo prevent the "black screen" crashes and state corruption identified in previous testing, the connection provider must be initialized at the root of the application.\n\nChain Configuration: Explicitly define SCAI Mainnet and Testnet parameters.\n\nRPC Fallback: Use the Thirdweb RPC URL as the default transport to ensure unauthenticated users can still view the market data.\n\nTheme Integration: Pass a custom darkTheme object to the RainbowKitProvider that overrides default rounded corners and bold weights to match the project's technical monospace style.\n\n3. CONNECTION WORKFLOWS\nA. The "Auth Guard" Logic\nThe frontend must strictly gate certain functionalities based on the connection state provided by the useAccount hook.\n\nDashboard: If !isConnected, the UI renders an "Authentication Required" placeholder instead of attempting to fetch empty personal holdings.\n\nMinting: Form inputs and the "Mint & List" button are hard-disabled until a valid signer is detected.\n\nB. Transaction Flow Handling\n\nRequest: User initiates a transaction (e.g., buying the Genesis Fragment // SV-01).\n\nSignature State: Monitor the useWriteContract status.\n\nError Catching: Wrap the connection logic in try/catch blocks to specifically handle UserRejectedRequestError. This prevents the app from hanging or crashing if a user closes the wallet popup without signing.\n\n4. MOBILE-SPECIFIC OPTIMIZATIONS\nGiven the "crowded" nature of mobile Web3 headers, the connection UI follows these responsive rules:\n\nDynamic Visibility: On viewports under 768px, the primary "Connect Wallet" button is moved from the header row into the hamburger navigation menu to preserve logo spacing.\n\nCoarse Pointer Handling: Detect touch devices to disable custom pointer/dot effects that often get "stuck" when a user taps the screen.\n\nWalletConnect Modal: Ensure the projectId is correctly configured in Wagmi to trigger deep-linking for mobile wallets (MetaMask Mobile, Coinbase Wallet App).\n\n5. SECURITY & SESSION PERSISTENCE\nAuto-Connect: Enable the reconnectOnMount feature in Wagmi to maintain sessions across page refreshes.\n\nSanitization: All addresses retrieved from useAccount are treated as untrusted inputs. Use checksummed addresses for on-chain queries.\n\nPrivacy: Ensure no sensitive wallet metadata or transaction history is logged to external analytics or Vercel runtime logs.\n\n6. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS\nVerify the projectId from WalletConnect Cloud is active and added to the .env file.\n\nApply the whitespace-nowrap and text-xs CSS fixes to the mobile navbar button to prevent text-wrapping bugs.\n\nTest the "Connection Termination" flow (closing the modal mid-process) to ensure the React Error Boundary catches the rejection.\n\nStandardize all button text to "Connect Wallet" for UI consistency.	2026-05-02 19:01:21.819514
