ce470978-9824-498a-9f5f-a6c7a437ca6d	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	ce255a5b-5d74-4a7d-a9c8-844215d09233	task	2026-05-02 14:39:15.971	2026-05-03 01:33:27.076	654	1. TESTING ENVIRONMENT SETUP\nFramework: Hardhat (Local Network)\n\nAssertion Library: Chai (via @nomicfoundation/hardhat-chai-matchers)\n\nTesting Accounts: Hardhat provides 20 local signers (Deployer, Buyer, Seller, etc.).\n\nCommand: npx hardhat test\n\n2. CORE TEST SUITES (test/market-test.js)\nA. Deployment & Initialization\n\nShould deploy successfully and assign the correct owner address.\n\nShould set the correct default listingPrice (e.g., 0.001 ether).\n\nB. Minting (createToken)\n\nShould increment the token ID and assign it to the contract address.\n\nShould correctly map the IPFS tokenURI.\n\nShould emit the MarketItemCreated event with correct struct data.\n\nShould fail if msg.value does not equal the protocol listing fee.\n\nC. Purchasing (createMarketSale)\n\nShould transfer the exact SCAI value to the seller.\n\nShould transfer the protocol fee to the contract owner.\n\nShould transfer the NFT custody from the contract to the buyer.\n\nShould update the sold boolean to true in the MarketItem mapping.\n\nShould emit the MarketItemSold event.\n\n3. SECURITY & EDGE CASES (CRITICAL)\nSelf-Buy Prevention (Bug Fix Verify):\n\nTest: Connect as User A -> Mint Asset -> User A attempts to call createMarketSale.\n\nAssertion: await expect(...).to.be.revertedWith("Protocol Constraint: Cannot purchase your own listed asset.")\n\nInsufficient Funds:\n\nTest: Buyer attempts to purchase with msg.value less than price.\n\nAssertion: Must revert.\n\nDouble Spend / Already Sold:\n\nTest: Buyer B attempts to purchase an asset immediately after Buyer A.\n\nAssertion: Must revert (item no longer exists in active mapping or is owned by Buyer A).\n\n4. ACTION ITEMS\nWrite the initial deployment setup block inside describe("ProvenanceMarket", function () { ... }) using Hardhat's loadFixture for faster test execution.\n\nDraft the "Self-Buy" edge case first to verify the previous patch.\n\nRun npx hardhat coverage to ensure 100% path coverage on state-mutating functions before SCAI Testnet deployment.	2026-05-02 20:09:15.973132
3e44cb11-8d4f-4bb6-82da-9d36ea0e722c	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	23bff0ae-8a52-4cd8-ae99-f0052821df6e	task	2026-05-03 02:18:32.861	2026-05-03 03:32:56.349	74	1. SMART CONTRACT OPTIMIZATIONS (Solidity)\nCustom Errors: Replaced standard require("Error string") statements with Custom Errors (e.g., error Unauthorized()) to significantly reduce deployment and execution gas costs.\n\nVariable Caching: Updated functions to cache state variables in memory before executing loops or multiple reads, minimizing expensive SLOAD operations.\n\nStruct Packing: Audited the MarketItem struct to ensure variables are tightly packed into 256-bit storage slots where possible.\n\nCalldata vs Memory: Switched function parameters from memory to calldata on external functions (like passing the tokenURI) to save gas on memory allocation.\n\n2. FRONTEND & RPC PERFORMANCE (React)\nRPC Batching: Investigating Multicall integration to batch read requests on the /explore page, reducing network calls to the Thirdweb RPC.\n\nIPFS Caching Optimization: Tightened React Query staleTime and cacheTime configurations to prevent redundant calls to the Pinata gateway for already-resolved metadata.\n\nAsset Lazy Loading: Enforced loading="lazy" and decoding optimization on all NFT image renders to prevent main-thread blocking during initial page load.\n\n3. IMMEDIATE ACTION ITEMS\nRun npx hardhat-gas-reporter to benchmark the exact gas cost of createMarketSale and createToken before and after the custom error patch.\n\nMonitor Vercel analytics for the Time to Interactive (TTI) metric on mobile devices.\n\nVerify that the Wagmi configuration is utilizing WebSocket connections where applicable for faster event listening.	2026-05-03 07:48:32.861882
f03f8ee6-493e-4d10-a77a-72c2a2df81d9	775fa188-9b39-44be-bb77-7238179e139b	01a3ab77-5511-43ba-a356-64b2175740b9	task	2026-05-03 01:33:29.528	2026-05-03 02:18:28.38	44	1. SECURITY THREATS & MITIGATIONS\nReentrancy: Mitigated using OpenZeppelin's nonReentrant modifier on all value-transferring functions (createMarketSale). State updates precede external calls.\n\nFront-Running: Handled via SCAI network transaction ordering.\n\nSelf-Purchase Exploit: Patched on-chain via require(msg.sender != seller).\n\n2. EDGE-CASE HANDLING\nInsufficient SCAI: Transactions blocked by Wagmi gas estimation pre-signature and msg.value == price on-chain.\n\nRace Conditions (Ghost Listings): If two users buy simultaneously, the slower transaction reverts (sold == true), triggering React Query to invalidate and refresh the UI.\n\nIPFS Gateway Timeout: resolveIPFS utility intercepts failures and renders a "Metadata Unavailable" placeholder without blocking the DOM.\n\nWallet Rejection: try/catch wrappers around Wagmi hooks intercept UserRejectedRequestError to prevent black-screen crashes.\n\n3. ACTION ITEMS\nExecute npx hardhat test to validate the msg.sender != seller patch and insufficient funds reversion.\n\nManually trigger a MetaMask "Reject Signature" event on the frontend to verify UI stability.\n\nForce an IPFS timeout by temporarily corrupting the VITE_PINATA_GATEWAY_URL string to test image fallbacks.	2026-05-03 07:03:29.529191
