2100725e-83b3-4d18-b19d-987b14bff7cb	fe8eb7b2-7509-416a-aa7c-39bb7fb9152d	aec1af16-d287-4a4f-b0d7-c9213db3d05b	task	2026-05-05 08:40:27.772	2026-05-05 09:44:04.005	63	For security and edge-case testing of smart contracts, I would focus on identifying vulnerabilities, validating safe execution, and ensuring correct behavior under abnormal conditions.\n\nI would begin by testing common security risks such as reentrancy attacks, integer overflow/underflow, improper access control, and denial-of-service scenarios. This includes verifying that only authorized users can execute sensitive functions and that contract state cannot be manipulated unexpectedly.\n\nNext, I would design edge-case tests by providing boundary and invalid inputs, such as zero values, extremely large values, and unexpected transaction sequences. I would also simulate multiple users interacting with the contract to observe behavior under concurrent conditions.\n\nI would use testing frameworks like Hardhat or Truffle to automate these tests, along with assertion libraries to validate expected outcomes. Additionally, I would check for correct handling of revert conditions and ensure that all failure cases are properly managed.\n\nWhere applicable, I would use static analysis tools and security best practices to further identify potential vulnerabilities.\nOverall, the goal is to ensure the contract is secure, resilient, and behaves correctly under both normal and adversarial conditions before deployment.	2026-05-05 14:10:27.77363
